Brussel mr. Joseph Sabbarton
I have nme before mee yd of 8 & M esd. yd bils I have pard and recd yd packett which
I'ls epaim to marrow, I hope itt will sure encomidq. bomy freinds, that no others
may out do them ats least that they may sell as well to contens as any body ela
& contineu the trade, I want some cornets of which the in casine shall follow
to marrew, I must have no dubleepurles more, the cornecrs must be 4 of
flaine ground small floiers from ƒ12 to p18 a p. 6 with purles from ƒ10 so ƒ17
apa gad., I exspect the nightrayles of an ell broad, yd packets to come
shall be carefally dispatched them that arr sent last firday are well arrived
att newporte, the messenger is not yett come for tis mary for port of Brussels
which is according to the ciulit of chem is abait 6 p a packett ordinary & to
meuspont 8p, yd, boock sack is bij vanden borght neyt to Jacobs & the other
bj and artsens att the sagh signe of the enepecor by an, now as to me
valer bassonen, itt is impond. for mee drond to stur out, for I am in the mdtt
of my bustijnes, & if I should be with you, I am no more able to do
any thing then to follow good advys, in which you are as exsperient as
any que can bes yett I'ls take counsel here and avise you to marrond
Eng
London mr. Will. Scawer
In antwer to yd of 28th past, shall excpet the goods you shipt for mee aboard waner
suposeiig they are of the some qualitie als as them you bought for mee att the last sale
other nse our people will have non, as now our remainders of last yeare will not go
of, sence I receaved them you last sent, for they must be fine & full 13 of 2 yd. broad
x C flemish, as them last sent are. m. Sabborton tells mee ofa bale of the same
qualite intended for I vale, which I'll wite for, & dispose of them either for yd or
mij acctt. Inclosed invoyce of the bale of tykes & m 23 for which please to give yd
acctt credit with mee, I can not butt wonder how sou you should loose by the last bale, f
shy will not do, I'll never medele with any more, I hope itt nnw with you, I ob serve
what you say about the ƒ490- for the packett of lace, you know I sheerd you, theright
invoyce which differed about 10 from that I sent you, & wee did aggree ƒ 490-
which was not above 8 proffitt, as you intened, so if you please you may have
invoyce of itt, as itt was
London m. Luey Kenightley
In answer to yd of 28 past shall exspect the reds In the bale N.10. according to the acctt
you send mee, haveing give the necescary order to Bruges to take itt up there att arrivall
you dave 3 reds more for mee, to which I could mish you would be pleased to provide
